Navigate to other release versions of Doxee Platform Process Engine

[6.6](https://docs.doxee.com/docs/en/process-engine-6-6)

[6.7](https://docs.doxee.com/docs/en/process-engine-6-7)

**File:** watcher.ipd

**Shows:** File wait type, watcher loop, call separate process from within process

**Components:** Start Element, Wait Element, Loop, executeProcess Activity, Decision, End Element, Connection

**Process parameters:** directory, template_url

This process runs continuously and watches for files with the ending ".xml" to appear in the directory specified by the process parameter "directory". For each file it finds, a new PDF Generate process (see [PDF Generate](/doxee-platform/docs/chapter-4-pdf-generate)) is started. The URL of the file is passed as parameter "xml_url". The location of a template has to be provided when launching the watcher as parameter "template_url". The PDF Generate process creates and saves a PDF for each XML with the same name and under the same directory as the XML.
